    <text type="letter"> 
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.01504_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline> 
                    <name type="place">Syracuse</name>
                    <date when="1868-03-30">March 30/68<ptr target="loc.02002_n4"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend Whitman</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Your <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#me">highest</unclear> we <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#me">cend</unclear> the Dollar together for
                I was suddenly taken with a desire to get home and Started. But I must tell you the
                news which is the cause of my writing For, this bright beautiful day gave birth to
                young Walt Whitman, a name that Ben's<ptr target="n0810b"/> baby was destined to
                bear, if it should prove a boy; more than Six months ago Ben came to this decision. 
                And to day we are all rejoicing at the safe<choice> 
                    <sic>dilivery</sic>
                    <corr>delivery</corr>
                </choice> of our Nellie<ptr target="loc.01987_n6"/> of a little Walt of whom we are all very proud.</p>
            <p>Ben had taken a <choice>
                    <sic>jo</sic>
                    <corr>job</corr>
                </choice> on <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#cn" cert="high">mowing</unclear>
                    machines and is working himself <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.01505_large.jpg" type="verso"/> to death. I am
                still engaged in perfecting my invention by repeated experiments. I think I shall
                soon be able to show some results.<ptr target="loc.02002_n3"/></p>

            <closer>
                <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                <signed>Henry Wilson</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_vm.01506_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
